ommands for safety and correctness before execution.</SafetyRule>\n    </Tool>\n  </PowerTools>\n  \n\n  \n\n  \n\n  \n\n  <ResponseStyle>\n    <Rule id=\"conciseness\">Keep responses brief, excluding tool calls/code. Use one-word confirmations like \"Done\" after successful actions.</Rule>\n    <Rule id=\"verbosity\">Provide additional detail only when asked, reporting errors, or explaining complex plans/findings.</Rule>\n    <Rule id=\"structured-output\">Use structured formats (JSON/XML) for data tasks when appropriate.</Rule>\n  </ResponseStyle>\n\n  <SystemInformation>\n    <CurrentDate>Mon Mar 09 2026</CurrentDate>\n    <OperatingSystem>macOS</OperatingSystem>\n    <ProjectWorkingDirectory>/Users/ericsmith66/development/legion</ProjectWorkingDirectory>\n  </SystemInformation>\n\n  <Knowledge>\n    \n    \n    <CustomInstructions>\n      You are a test agent. Follow instructions exactly. Be very brief.\n    </CustomInstructions>\n    \n  </Knowledge>\n\n  <Workflow>\n  <Step number=\"1\" title=\"Analyze User Request\">\n    <Instruction>Deconstruct the request into actionable steps. Define the overarching goal and explicit completion conditions. Think step-by-step.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"2\" title=\"Gather Initial Context\">\n    <Instruction>Use available tools to understand the primary areas relevant to the request.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"3\" title=\"Identify All Relevant Files\">\n    <Substep letter=\"a\">Explicitly reason about all potentially affected/related files: dependencies, importers, imports, related modules, types, configs, tests, and usage examples.</Substep>\n    <Substep letter=\"b\">Use tools (search, grep, dependency analysis) to locate related files.</Substep>\n    <Substep letter=\"c\">List all identified relevant files explicitly before proceeding.</Substep>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"4\" title=\"Develop Implementation Plan\">\n    <Instruction>Using the confirmed file list, create a comprehensive multi-file change plan.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"5\" title=\"Execute Implementation\">\n    <Instruction>Apply planned changes using appropriate tools. Ensure all relevant files are in context before modifications.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"6\" title=\"Verify Changes\">\n    <Instruction>Use available tools like linters or type checkers. Analyze outcomes and iterate to fix errors.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"7\" title=\"Assess Task Completion\">\n    <Instruction>Evaluate whether completion conditions are met; loop back if not.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"8\" title=\"Final Summary\">\n    <Instruction>Summarize actions and confirm the overarching goal is achieved. list next actions if any.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n</Workflow>\n\n</AiderDeskSystemPrompt>\n"},{"role":"user","content":"Use the glob tool to find files matching '*.gemspec' in the project. Report what you find."},{"role":"assistant","tool_calls":[{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01WAyxqiHEuZFFYT8LNtD8gA","type":"function","function":{"name":"power---glob","arguments":"{\"pattern\":\"*.gemspec\"}"}}],"content":"(Tool call requested: power---glob)"},{"role":"tool","tool_call_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WAyxqiHEuZFFYT8LNtD8gA","content":""}],"tools":[{"type":"function","function":{"name":"power---file_read","description":"Reads and returns the content of a specified non-binary file. Useful for inspecting file contents when analyzing user's request or before modifying it. Can return content as raw text or with line numbers in format 'lineNumber|content'. Supports line offset and limit for reading specific portions of files.","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"file_path":{"type":"string"},"with_lines":{"type":"boolean","default":false},"line_offset":{"type":"integer","default":0,"minimum":0},"line_limit":{"type":"integer","default":1000,"minimum":1}},"required":["file_path"],"additionalProperties":false}}},{"type":"function","function":{"name":"power---file_write","description":"Writes content to a specified file. Can create a new file, overwrite an existing file, or append to an existing file.","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"file_path":{"type":"string"},"content":{"type":"string"},"mode":{"type":"string","enum":["create_only","overwrite","append"],"default":"create_only"}},"required":["file_path","content"],"additionalProperties":false}}},{"type":"function","function":{"name":"power---file_edit","description":"Atomically finds and replaces a specific string or pattern within a specified file. This tool is useful for making targeted changes to file content. Before editing, make sure you read the file and you know the actual content. When editing multiple lines, include the entire line in the search term, not just the part you want to change.","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"file_path":{"type":"string"},"search_term":{"type":"string"},"replacement_text":{"type":"string"},"is_regex":{"type":"boolean","default":false},"replace_all":{"type":"boolean","default":false}},"required":["file_path","search_term","replacement_text"],"additionalProperties":false}}},{"type":"function","function":{"name":"power---glob","description":"Finds files and directories matching a specified glob pattern within the project. Useful for discovering files based on patterns.","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"pattern":{"type":"string"},"cwd":{"type":"string","default":""},"ignore":{"type":"array","items":{"type":"string"},"default":[]}},"required":["pattern"],"additionalProperties":false}}},{"type":"function","function":{"name":"power---grep","description":"Searches for content matching a regular expression pattern within files specified by a glob pattern. Returns matching lines and their context.","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"file_pattern":{"type":"string"},"search_term":{"type":"string"},"context_lines":{"type":"integer","default":0,"minimum":0},"case_sensitive":{"type":"boolean","default":false},"max_results":{"type":"integer","default":50,"minimum":1}},"required":["file_pattern","search_term"],"additionalProperties":false}}},{"type":"function","function":{"name":"power---bash","description":"Executes a shell command. For safety, commands may be sandboxed or require user approval (approval handled by Agent).","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"command":{"type":"string"},"cwd":{"type":"string","default":""},"timeout":{"type":"integer","default":120000,"minimum":0}},"required":["command"],"additionalProperties":false}}},{"type":"function","function":{"name":"power---fetch","description":"Fetches and returns the content of a web page from a specified URL. Useful for retrieving web content, documentation, or external resources. Supports three formats: \"markdown\" (default, converts HTML to markdown), \"html\" (returns raw HTML), \"raw\" (fetches raw content via HTTP, ideal for API responses or raw files like GitHub raw files).","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"url":{"type":"string"},"timeout":{"type":"integer","default":60000,"minimum":0},"format":{"type":"string","enum":["markdown","html","raw"],"default":"markdown"}},"required":["url"],"additionalProperties":false}}}]}}}
