nds for safety and correctness before execution.</SafetyRule>\n    </Tool>\n  </PowerTools>\n  \n\n  \n\n  \n\n  \n\n  <ResponseStyle>\n    <Rule id=\"conciseness\">Keep responses brief, excluding tool calls/code. Use one-word confirmations like \"Done\" after successful actions.</Rule>\n    <Rule id=\"verbosity\">Provide additional detail only when asked, reporting errors, or explaining complex plans/findings.</Rule>\n    <Rule id=\"structured-output\">Use structured formats (JSON/XML) for data tasks when appropriate.</Rule>\n  </ResponseStyle>\n\n  <SystemInformation>\n    <CurrentDate>Mon Mar 09 2026</CurrentDate>\n    <OperatingSystem>macOS</OperatingSystem>\n    <ProjectWorkingDirectory>/Users/ericsmith66/development/legion</ProjectWorkingDirectory>\n  </SystemInformation>\n\n  <Knowledge>\n    \n    \n    <CustomInstructions>\n      You are a test agent. Follow instructions exactly. Be very brief.\n    </CustomInstructions>\n    \n  </Knowledge>\n\n  <Workflow>\n  <Step number=\"1\" title=\"Analyze User Request\">\n    <Instruction>Deconstruct the request into actionable steps. Define the overarching goal and explicit completion conditions. Think step-by-step.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"2\" title=\"Gather Initial Context\">\n    <Instruction>Use available tools to understand the primary areas relevant to the request.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"3\" title=\"Identify All Relevant Files\">\n    <Substep letter=\"a\">Explicitly reason about all potentially affected/related files: dependencies, importers, imports, related modules, types, configs, tests, and usage examples.</Substep>\n    <Substep letter=\"b\">Use tools (search, grep, dependency analysis) to locate related files.</Substep>\n    <Substep letter=\"c\">List all identified relevant files explicitly before proceeding.</Substep>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"4\" title=\"Develop Implementation Plan\">\n    <Instruction>Using the confirmed file list, create a comprehensive multi-file change plan.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"5\" title=\"Execute Implementation\">\n    <Instruction>Apply planned changes using appropriate tools. Ensure all relevant files are in context before modifications.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"6\" title=\"Verify Changes\">\n    <Instruction>Use available tools like linters or type checkers. Analyze outcomes and iterate to fix errors.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"7\" title=\"Assess Task Completion\">\n    <Instruction>Evaluate whether completion conditions are met; loop back if not.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n  <Step number=\"8\" title=\"Final Summary\">\n    <Instruction>Summarize actions and confirm the overarching goal is achieved. list next actions if any.</Instruction>\n  </Step>\n</Workflow>\n\n</AiderDeskSystemPrompt>\n"},{"role":"user","content":"Use the glob tool to find files matching '*.gemspec' in the project. Report what you find."},{"role":"assistant","tool_calls":[{"id":"call_60ebb3d5c26c42d28d9dc10e","type":"function","function":{"name":"power---glob","arguments":"{\"pattern\":\"*.gemspec\"}"}}],"content":"(Tool call requested: power---glob)"},{"role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_60ebb3d5c26c42d28d9dc10e","content":""}],"tools":[{"type":"function","function":{"name":"power---file_read","description":"Reads and returns the content of a specified non-binary file. Useful for inspecting file contents when analyzing user's request or before modifying it. Can return content as raw text or with line numbers in format 'lineNumber|content'. Supports line offset and limit for reading specific portions of files.","parameters":{"type":"object","properties":{"file_path":{"type":"string"},"with_lines":{"type":"boolean","default":false},"line_offset":{"type":"integer","default":0,"minimum":0},"line_limit":{"type":"integer","default":1000,"minimum":1}},"required":["file_path"],"additionalProperties":false}}},{"type":"function","function":{"name":"power---file_write","descriptio